# 4. 進む足を止めるもの

Emu: (How do we save Kikyogumi from being disbanded...?)
Emu: (They're making that announcement in three weeks, so we gotta come up with something before then.)
Emu: (Let's see... What if we got robots like Robo-Nene to replace any troupe members that left?)
Emu: (I mean, she can do all sorts of things like jumping really high and moving super fast.)
Emu: (But that doesn't really fit what Morinomiya's going for...)
Emu: (I've been thinking really hard since then... But I haven't been able to come up with any good ideas...)
Emu: Nooo! Why can't I just easy-peasy-lemon-squeezy ideas out of my brain?!
???: E-Easy-peasy-lemon-squeezy...?
Emu: Huh?
Emu: KAITO...
KAITO: I was worried that you weren't feeling well when I saw you curled up on a bench like this...
KAITO: But that doesn't appear to be the case.
Emu: So, umm...
KAITO: Is something bothering you...?
Emu: Oh...
KAITO: I'll be more than happy to listen. But you don't have to tell me if you don't feel comfortable, Emu.
Emu: Thanks, KAITO. The thing is...
KAITO: I see... And you're trying to come up with a way to save Kikyogumi now.
Emu: *Nod* At first, I thought we could try to get the Suzurangumi fans to start liking them.
Emu: My hope was that they'd start liking Kikyogumi since they already like going to see shows.
Emu: But...
Emu: Both troupes have to share the same theatre.
Emu: And because of that, Suzurangumi hasn't been able to put on as many performances.
Emu: Which has made a lot of their fans really sad and disappointed.
KAITO: I see...
KAITO: If that's the case, then some Suzurangumi fans might hold a very negative opinion of Kikyogumi.
Emu: *Nod*
Emu: There are a lot of other things that I have to keep in mind too...
Emu: So, I'm starting to wonder if I'm ever going to come up with an idea that's going to make everyone smile.
Emu: But I really don't want Kikyogumi to get disbanded!
KAITO: ...!
Emu: Because the show we saw them put on was so amazing...
Emu: Even after they closed the curtains, my heart was still racing. I didn't want it to end...
Emu: That's why I believe Kikyogumi can make lots and lots more people smile.
Emu: So...
Emu: Saving them isn't going to be easy, but I'm still gonna do my best.
KAITO: It sounds like you know what you want to do, Emu.
Emu: Hehe. Yup!
Emu: I felt like I was running in circles, but my head feels a lot clearer after talking to you, KAITO!
KAITO: That's good to hear.
KAITO: All I can really do is listen to your concerns, Emu, but I'll be rooting for you...
Emu: *Nod* Thanks, KAITO!
Byakkomachi: ...
Byakkomachi: This is incredible... You really came up with all these ideas in that short period?
Emu: Yup...! I wrote down everything that popped into my head!
Emu: You probably came up with some of the same ideas already, but do you see any that might be worth giving a try...?
Byakkomachi: ...
Byakkomachi: Each one is fun and creative, but I'm not sure we have the time or budget to make them happen...
Emu: Right...
Byakkomachi: I'm sorry... I know you worked hard to come up with these.
Emu: No, that's okay! I'd rather you tell me straight out that they aren't possible!
Emu: Still, this is so hard... If we don't hurry, then Kikyogumi is really gonna be disbanded...
Byakkomachi: I know. After they announce what's happening, it's going to be next to impossible to get them to take it back.
Byakkomachi: And I'm also having trouble coming up with the perfect solution. But I am certain that getting young people to start supporting the troupe is going to play a key role...
Emu: Oh, wait...! Ms. Suzu, I have a question! They're really popular with young people, right?
Emu: Would it be possible to lower ticket prices somehow?
Emu: Right now, you have to pay the same price as a Suzurangumi show... But if you want more young people to come, then lower might be the way to go.
Emu: That should make it easier for people to invite their friends to come along!
Byakkomachi: I've already come up with a similar idea, and even suggested it to the board. They rejected it outright...
Byakkomachi: Without some way to bring new or existing fans in droves, lowering ticket prices would simply result in a drop in revenue.
Byakkomachi: That would mean a smaller budget for each show...resulting in lower quality performances. Morinomiya is firmly against that.
Byakkomachi: Because they want to provide the audience with the best experience imaginable. Morinomiya has existed for a hundred years precisely because it's been doing just that.
Emu: Right...
Emu: (I think I'm starting to get a better idea of what the people running Morinomiya care about the most.)
Emu: (But...)
Emu: You can still put on amazing performances without money, right...?
Byakkomachi: Huh...?
Emu: The Wonder Stage used to get almost no funding. We had to make things ourselves for a while...
Emu: We even repaired all the old seats that were there ourselves.
Emu: What if we all worked together and came up with ways for the audience to have fun?
Emu: Wouldn't that make it possible to give them the best experience imaginable, while also lowering ticket prices...?
Byakkomachi: ...
Byakkomachi: In theory, that may be possible.
Emu: Then...!
Byakkomachi: But that's only in theory. We have no idea what's going to happen if we put your idea into practice...
Emu: Yeah, I know... But...
Emu: But if there is a possibility, then we should try to think it through.
Emu: If you lock down all the little details and make the suggestion based on that, maybe it'll go better this time!
Byakkomachi: I know. I've been telling myself the same thing...
Byakkomachi: But... The truth is...
Byakkomachi: I'm really scared.
Emu: What...?
Byakkomachi: Morinomiya needs to change if it's going to exist in the future.
Byakkomachi: In that sense, I don't regret pushing for the formation of Kikyogumi.
Byakkomachi: However...
Byakkomachi: That decision ended up disappointing some of our existing fans.
Emu: (Oh...)
Emu: You mean how when it was decided that two troupes would be sharing the theatre, it came as a huge disappointment to the Suzurangumi fans?
Byakkomachi: Yes. I honestly wasn't expecting that to happen.
Byakkomachi: I should've seen that coming...
Byakkomachi: I know this is foolish of me... No change is going to have a 100% approval rating.
Byakkomachi: But the thought of ending up saddening even more people...
Byakkomachi: I can't get that out of my head... I think I'm frozen with fear at this point.
Emu: ...
Emu: (I know what she means...)
Emu: (Trying to get Morinomiya to move forward might mean disappointing even more fans...)
KAITO: <...>
